      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T13:17:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The cros_config CLI is used to query it. For example \"cros_config / name\" returns the product name. We also query usb/mipi camera existence in autocaps here:\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/platform/tast/src/chromiumos/tast/autocaps/detect.go;l\u003d59\n\nThe configs for each board is put in model.yaml files based on the schema. Hatch for example:\n(public) https://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/overlays/overlay-hatch/chromeos-base/chromeos-config-bsp-hatch/files/model.yaml\n(private) https://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_internal/src/private-overlays/overlay-hatch-private/chromeos-base/chromeos-config-bsp-hatch-private/files/model.yaml\n\nOr in newer platforms, they are being migrated to use src/project/\u003cboard\u003e/\u003cmodel\u003e/config.star to generate the configs.\n\nBtw, do you want to skip boards without hardware switch? I think we should also test the negative cases.",
      "parentUuid": "ad90c078_a71357c0",
      "revId": "d44c2d655a9b9d221c3a87edabf1c9229e30e717",
