      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T14:55:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That means back to the drawing board I guess :).\n\nI have pushed  new version of this patches that uses crosconfig instead of dmidecode. Not exactly what you are proposing, but something in the better direction I hope.\n\nOn thing that I like from the current setup is that it does not test on hardware that does not have the privacy_switch, and I still catch the non-defined errors with avtest_label_detect: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform2/+/2558239\n\nWith your proposal, the test will run in all the boards.\n\nA non-related question. What is the benefit of using crosconfig vs HardwareDeps. Is there a document of when to use crosconfig vs HardwareDeps vs Autocaps ?\n\n\nThanks :)",
      "parentUuid": "873342f3_526b77a6",
